 Phase 1 reviewers of the ENDF/B-VI standards cross sections have  225 1451
 expressed the concern that the uncertainties resulting from the   225 1451
 combination of R-matrix and simultaneous evaluations might have   225 1451
 led to uncertainties that are too small.  As a result, the        225 1451
 Standards Subcommittee produced (at the May, 1990 CSEWG meeting)  225 1451
 a set of expanded covariance estimates for the standard cross     225 1451
 section reactions.  These uncertainties are estimates such that   225 1451
 if a modern day experiment were performed on a given standard     225 1451
 cross section using the best techniques, approximately 2/3 of     225 1451
 the results should fall within these expanded uncertainties. The  225 1451
 expanded uncertainties for the He-3(n,p) cross section are as     225 1451
